{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDA5MDU2NDM2", "number": 788, "title": "Fix CircleCI config to comply with Gradle docs", "bodyText": "Signed-off-by: Horacio Mijail Anton Quiles hmijail@gmail.com\n\n\nPR description\nRemoving ineffective/redundant/not recommended settings:\n\nIf parallel running is enabled in GRADLE_OPTS, it's not needed in the command lines.\nDisabling the gradle daemon goes against the recommendations of the Gradle docs.\nSetting -Xmx in GRADLE_OPTS is useless, according to Gradle docs.\n\nI tried moving -Xmx somewhere more appropriate, but the purpose is not clear anyway. My understanding is that the goal is to limit memory usage to avoid Out Of Memory errors in CircleCI. But for that, the Gradle defaults (which are currently in effect, since the setting isn't being applied) are more strict, so it wouldn't be helpful to apply the setting without serious review.\nFixed Issue(s)", "createdAt": "2020-04-26T10:12:54Z", "url": "https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/788", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "83fb2cfc76a001799d61dd1e7fb76164b1012799"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-04-30T15:46:03Z", "author": {"login": "hmijail"}, "timelineItems": {"totalCount": 9, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABcbX2EtgH2gAyNDA5MDU2NDM2OjAyNzJjZmI4YmM0NzgwZDExMTFjZDFkMzkwMzU3NmNkNjk0ZTI2MWI=", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABccupgkAH2gAyNDA5MDU2NDM2OjY3N2Y4NjNhNjI2NzdjZDU2ZmJkZjRkODQzY2RjMGJkM2ZhODcwMWQ=", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "0272cfb8bc4780d1111cd1d3903576cd694e261b", "author": {"user": {"login": "hmijail", "name": "Horacio Mijail Ant\u00f3n Quiles"}}, "url": "https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/commit/0272cfb8bc4780d1111cd1d3903576cd694e261b", "committedDate": "2020-04-26T10:08:55Z", "message": "Fix CircleCI config to comply with Gradle docs\n\nSigned-off-by: Horacio Mijail Anton Quiles <hmijail@gmail.com>"}}, {"